universum.studios.android.officium.service

Class ServiceError

  • java.lang.Object
    • universum.studios.android.officium.service.BaseServiceObject
      • universum.studios.android.officium.service.ServiceError
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ServiceObject

    public class ServiceError
extends BaseServiceObject
    A BaseServiceObject implementation that represents an error occurred during service execution. Service error may be defined as error response send by the server where in such case the error/response code may be obtained via getErrorCode() along with the error body via getErrorBody() respectively. Or it may be defined as a failure that has caused the associated service and request to fail. In such case isFailure() will return true and the occurred failure may be obtained via getFailure().
    Author:
    Martin Albedinsky
